We're using OnDemand (6.3-OD-06-017) and currently if you favorite a build plan that hasn't been executed yet, the entire Bamboo Build Status gadget shows up blank and throws a JavaScript exception:

{code:javascript}
Cannot read property 'state' of undefined
{code}

It appears the problem is here:

{code:javascript}
if (l.result) {
    j = l.result[0];
    r = j.state
} else {
    r = "Non executed"
}
{code}

l.result is defined, but l.result[0] is not. Not a big issue, but threw me off for a little bit as to why the page was sometimes blank.

Could you add email notification to change on plan status? 

Sample events from audit log, that should be able to trigger notification:
{noformat}
08:07, 13 Jun	 SYSTEM 	   	Plan 'BANMS-SONAR' detected that the repository is invalid. The plan will be disabled. Error was: Cannot determine head revision of 'https://stash.url/config.git' on branch 'sample'. Branch has probably been removed.
08:07, 13 Jun	 SYSTEM 	   	suspendedFromBuilding	false	true
{noformat}

When a build fails with the following message on the summary:

{quote}
No failed tests found, a possible compilation error occurred.
{quote}

One currently has to manually go to the "Logs" tab and search for the error.

It would be message in the summary tab included a link which switched to the log tab and also focused/highlighted the error line.

When git checkout tasks configured to use HTTPS run, the user and password are exposed in {{ps aux}}:
{noformat}
bamboo     15138  0.0  0.0  86752  2224 ?        S    May20   0:00 git-remote-https https://gituser:XXXXXXXX@stash.int.XXXX.com/scm/consumer/XXXX.git https://gituser:XXXXXXXX@stash.int.XXXX.com/scm/consumer/XXXX.git
bamboo     15140  0.0  0.0   9852   468 ?        S    May20   0:00 git fetch-pack --stateless-rpc --lock-pack --include-tag --thin --no-progress --depth=1 https://gituser:XXXXXXXX@stash.int.XXXX.com/scm/consumer/XXXX.git
{noformat}

If a JIRA issue has optional system fields marked as required (E.g., *Fix Version/s* is a system field which is optional by default), or custom fields marked as required, they will not be listed in Bamboo side when trying to create a JIRA issue from a build. Hence, the issue creation will fail and a message like this will be displayed:
{quote}
Cannot create issue of type {{<type>}} as it requires the following fields: {{<list of fields>}}. Please create issue directly in JIRA.
Troubleshoot errors during issue creation
{quote}

This makes the issue creation feature useless.

In the server.xml file, we have a settings for maxSpareThreads which is currently set to 75. According to the [tomcat 5.5 docs|http://tomcat.apache.org/tomcat-5.5-doc/config/http.html], the value is defined as thus:
{quote}
The maximum number of unused request processing threads that will be allowed to exist until the thread pool starts stopping the unnecessary threads. The default value is 50.
{quote}

Now starting from tomcat 6, the parameter is being deprecated and such leaving it will just throw warnings in the logs:
{code}
Jun 03, 2014 5:18:10 PM org.apache.catalina.startup.SetAllPropertiesRule begin
WARNING: [SetAllPropertiesRule]{Server/Service/Connector} Setting property 'maxSpareThreads' to '75' did not find a matching property.
Jun 03, 2014 5:18:11 PM org.apache.catalina.core.StandardContext setPath
{code}

Since Bamboo is now bundled with tomcat 7, this can safely be removed.
